    "Paying no to attention Edgar was, who entirely altered so his by disguise as to defy, the recognition men seized two,i Sid and began to into drag him the. house forward sprang Edgar struck one and so them of a blow heavy in the face he released that his hold of andi Sid back against staggered wall. the a with Then fury shout of his drew he knife rushed and at. Edgar latter The also his snatched knife his from gleird, into it shifted his hand left, threw and the into himself boxing usual attitude with left his forward. footese Malt The his in paused This. rush of defence line altogether new was him. to had been He in many engaged fierce a fray, his but always opponents had himself like, with, fought in their knives their right hands.",
    "Paying no attention to Edgar, who was so entirely altered by his disguise as to defy recognition, the two men seized Sidi, and began to drag him into the house. Edgar sprang forward and struck one of them so heavy a blow in the face that he released his hold of Sidi and staggered back against the wall. Then with a shout of fury he drew his knife and rushed at Edgar. The latter also snatched his knife from his girdle, shifted it into his left hand, and threw himself into the usual boxing attitude with his left foot forward. The Maltese paused in his rush. This line of defence was altogether new to him. He had been engaged in many a fierce fray, but his opponents had always, like himself, fought with their knives in their right hands."
