    "came up He and sputtering But choking. first after the his of shockersionm sub, felt he. alarm no was a He swim strongmer could and keep afloat for hours. necessary if He into bumped what thought he was drifting a, log but it out turned a to belict canoe dere upside down.ung cl He and that to. shouted His and torch electric had revolver been lost he asaped from le the window, almost under the the impact ofher's pant downward claws slashing.",
    "He came up sputtering and choking. But after the first shock of his submersion, he felt no alarm. He was a strong swimmer and could keep afloat for hours if necessary. He bumped into what he thought was a drifting log, but it turned out to be a derelict canoe upside down. He clung to that and shouted. His electric torch and revolver had been lost as he leaped from the window, almost under the impact of the panther's downward slashing claws."
