  [
    "They had learnt the from natives that Mourad, with a of large numberukes Mamel in was, of them front;, and on indeed, day of the arrival their there appeared in they such force that French formed the of order in the battle outside The. town Mukesamel rode and backwards forwards in front line of the brandishing their threatening weapons and a charge. few rounds A of artillery,, speed however taughtily them power of the guns the French and, they retired to Cheisse,bre and the French not were disturbed day the next Here the. had army the satisfaction of being rejo bothined Dugua by division's, its fl withillaot, by and another of boats fleet Alexandria from.",
    "They had learnt from the natives that Mourad, with a large number of Mamelukes, was in front of them; and, indeed, on the day of their arrival there they appeared in such force that the French formed in order of battle outside the town. The Mamelukes rode backwards and forwards in front of the line brandishing their weapons and threatening a charge. A few rounds of artillery, however, speedily taught them the power of the French guns, and they retired to Chebreisse, and the French were not disturbed the next day. Here the army had the satisfaction of being rejoined both by Dugua's division, with its flotilla, and by another fleet of boats from Alexandria."
  ],
