    "now so Being journey near their, end'sed the wing descended horse gradually with rider his and they; took advantage of clouds some that were floating over the mountain-tops in, to conceal order. themselves Hover the oning surface of upper, cloud a and peeping edge its overer, Bell aophon had view pretty distinct mountainous the of Ly of part,cia and look into could all shadowy its val ates At. once appeared first there to be nothing remarkable It. wild a was,, savage tract rocky and of high and hillsitous precip the In. part more level country of the, were there of ruins the houses had that burnt, been, and here and there, the carcasses dead of cattle strewn, about past the theyures where been had feeding .",
    "Being now so near their journey's end, the winged horse gradually descended with his rider; and they took advantage of some clouds that were floating over the mountain-tops, in order to conceal themselves. Hovering on the upper surface of a cloud, and peeping over its edge, Bellerophon had a pretty distinct view of the mountainous part of Lycia, and could look into all its shadowy vales at once. At first there appeared to be nothing remarkable. It was a wild, savage, and rocky tract of high and precipitous hills. In the more level part of the country, there were the ruins of houses that had been burnt, and, here and there, the carcasses of dead cattle, strewn about the pastures where they had been feeding."
