    "wasn It’ easyt finding or anybody on that anything. dock The crowded were edges, people with was centre the filled with a confused mass of horses struggling truck and drivers shouting were all who anxious terribly to get, somewhere� and didnt seem� to the make progress least in all spite of noise. their-hands Deck were with busyunks and tr boxes, which they fastened a to pulley swung and out the over heads the of people, and then up and, again down into the hold in Once. a a whileansom h wr itsiggled the through way toays dr an let out passenger excited, who always acted as if he expected had to the boat find without gone him.",
    "It wasn’t easy finding anybody or anything on that dock. The edges were crowded with people, the centre was filled with a confused mass of struggling truck horses and shouting drivers who were all terribly anxious to get somewhere, and didn’t seem to make the least progress in spite of all their noise. Deck-hands were busy with trunks and boxes, which they fastened to a pulley and swung out over the heads of the people, and then up and down again, into the hold. Once in a while a hansom wriggled its way through the drays to let out an excited passenger, who always acted as if he had expected to find the boat gone without him."
  ],
  [
    "\" fatherThe of boys the was a manufacturer and was, of also president in bank the city the little lived they where bank A. a is place other where people money is's them kept for whenever, and people the who keep there money any need, and come they what they get need. When college left Tom he was taken into the bank before, and's Bill graduation advanced been had the to position ofier cash had and, a very married fine young woman cash The. is theier that has man of the charge money in the.  bank",
    "\"The father of the boys was a manufacturer, and was also president of the bank in the little city where they lived. A bank is a place where other people's money is kept for them, and whenever the people who keep money there need any, they come and get what they need. When Tom left college he was taken into the bank, and before Bill's graduation had been advanced to the position of cashier, and had married a very fine young woman. The cashier is the man that has charge of the money in the bank."
  ],
  [
    "pheus had Or walk first to and,, went as he the long up cavern dark, E with,iceuryd him, behind carefully ob heeyed till,, just as was he reaching the air upper unh, he forgotappily and turned, to head his whether see she were. following  just He saw her stretch out hands her him to, and she then drawn was back vanished and, his sight from.  The gates closed were he and, had lost her again . this After he sadly wandered about, his all to songs turned,oe w until last at the Bacchanal women, fury at in his despising the foul rites their of god tore, him limb from limb Mus. Thees collected his and, remains funeral them gave and rites, his Jupiter placed in lyre, the skies where you may it know by one of the all brightest of. stars our",
    "Orpheus had to walk first, and, as he went up the long, dark cavern, with Eurydice behind him, he carefully obeyed, till, just as he was reaching the upper air, he unhappily forgot, and turned his head to see whether she were following.  He just saw her stretch out her hands to him, and then she was drawn back, and vanished from his sight.  The gates were closed, and he had lost her again.  After this he wandered sadly about, all his songs turned to woe, until at last the Bacchanal women, in fury at his despising the foul rites of their god, tore him limb from limb. The Muses collected his remains, and gave them funeral rites, and Jupiter placed his lyre in the skies, where you may know it by one of the brightest of all our stars."
  ],
