    "wind continued The favour to us drawing, gradually west to the.ward  sight Weed red light a on Kinnaird Head,'s as, which got more we east to the changed,ward a to bright  colour. it was Beyondburgh. Fraser ha By  winduling our able were we steer for toay Head Rath. Near  caught we it In sight ofieverug Castle . We a gave berth to wide head, the which a from dangerous of reef rocks out run though for; ocean was the toler calmably we, could water the see over breaking them .",
    "The wind continued to favour us, drawing gradually to the westward.  We sighted a red light on Kinnaird's Head, which, as we got more to the eastward, changed to a bright colour.  Beyond it was Fraserburgh.  By hauling our wind we were able to steer for Rathay Head.  Near it we caught sight of Inverugie Castle.  We gave a wide berth to the head, from which a dangerous reef of rocks run out; for though the ocean was tolerably calm, we could see the water breaking over them."
  ],
